dunger
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:something old or unreliable, esp. an old car; something worn out or not of the first class; often collocated old dunger.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka dunga; this headword vehicles and machines; see also old dunger buildings
