Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 41
Edition:
Quote: dunga, dunger trrouble, in phr. in the dunga; perhaps extension of the word `dung'.  - dilapidated object, such as house, car or contraption, from engine going `dunga, dunga, dunga', the word serving to indicate the object is useless.
